HEADWORD: Subdititious
<hw>Sub`di*ti"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subdititius</ets>, <ets>subditicius</ets>, fr. <ets>subdere</ets>
to substitute.]</ety> <def>Put secretly in the place of something else;
